      "writtenOn": "2019-05-15T21:36:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So I think there is some confusion because fPathData is used to represent the 3 states a path can be in for the glyph.\n\n1) Not queried yet.\n2) Queried but the glyph has no path.\n3) Cached path is available.\n\nThe assert on hasPath says that we should have queried it before calling that method so it should return true if 3) and false if 2). I didn\u0027t realize this earlier since I only looked at the code which safely handles and returned false for the 1) case also.\n\nI\u0027ve replaced hasPath with an enum which explicitly returns one of the 3 states we\u0027re in. More details why are in the SkTypeface_remote code below.",
      "parentUuid": "d28c8f1a_2291373c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 178,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 178,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "6e26658c77b58e17a9e9cfbf4fb7662e1c8fbb7b",
