      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-15T13:43:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Needs checking for fallback only has to happen when we have never seen the glyph before. The fallback processing will then lookup the glyph on a different strike and send that information. We don\u0027t need to process fallback every single time.\n\nPlease see CL for how I think prepareForDrawing should look:\nhttps://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/213822",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 638,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 638,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "6e26658c77b58e17a9e9cfbf4fb7662e1c8fbb7b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8a266e06_3b28c08f",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRemoteGlyphCache.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 638,
      "author": {
        "id": 7830
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-15T21:36:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reason it needs to be done everytime is because each time its drawn we need to pin the fallback strike as well. Consider the following case:\n\n1) The first time the glyph is drawn, we find a cache miss here and add it for fallback processing. The painter code creates the fallback strike and adds the glyph that will actually be used for drawing to it.\n\n2) The next time the glyph with no path is cached but the fallback strike has been evicted. If we don\u0027t add the glyph for fallback processing since the no path glyph is cached, we\u0027d never regenerate the fallback strike.\n\nAnother thing I noticed about your change is that we\u0027re adding all glyphs to the returned list (not just the fallback ones). Why is that needed? I don\u0027t see anything else the painter needs to do for the other cases.",
      "parentUuid": "7df5ad17_936f84da",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 638,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 638,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "6e26658c77b58e17a9e9cfbf4fb7662e1c8fbb7b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
