      "writtenOn": "2019-05-15T21:36:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I can\u0027t use hasPath() because it requires that we must have queried the path before calling the method, and that is not necessarily true here. In fact I want to know if we\u0027re in the queried but no path state to distinguish them from real cache miss cases.\n\nAnother thing is that with the code in this patch which initializes the glyph with an empty path, to forward the renderer\u0027s info that there is no path, then SkStrike shouldn\u0027t call generatePath. The only case where it would happen is the |fGenerateImageFromPath| code in SkScalerContext which doesn\u0027t use the strike cache. I\u0027ve handled that in this patch as well.",
